{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6682bd6bba0e94a3c4025c87", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "", "questionLabels": [], "question": {"text": "A heavy iron bar of weight <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>kg</mi></math> is having its one end on the ground and the other on the shoulder of a man. The rod makes an angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo></math> with the horizontal, the normal force\u00a0applied\u00a0by the man on bar\u00a0is:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "7lLK6", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>kg</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>wt</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "u16kG", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>kg</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>wt</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "04nvu", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>kg</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>wt</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "l0oHS", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>kg</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>wt</mi></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p>Let's consider the following diagram:</p><p><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/b43a5fe3-8477-4795-9793-9a7c1c2e12d2.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 235px;\"/></p><p>For the equilibrium of the system, the net torque, according to the above figure, on the system about point\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>\u00a0should be zero.</p><p>With reference to the above figure, the net anti-clockwise torque about\u00a0<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>\u00a0is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>\u03c4</mi><mi>a</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>L</mi><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>1</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>And, the net clockwise torque about the same point is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>\u03c4</mi><mi>c</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>W</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>\u00a0</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mo>.</mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></math></p><p>Equations (1) and (2) imply that</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mi>cos</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>\u00d7</mo><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mi>L</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo><mo>\u00d7</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>L</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>\u21d2</mo><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>120</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>\u00d7</mo><mi>cos</mi><mn>60</mn><mo>\u00b0</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn></math></p><p>Hence, the required weight can be expressed as</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>\u00a0</mo><mi>kg</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>wt</mi></math></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "bucket": "Tough Ques (JEE Adv)", "concepts": [], "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ19563578", "subject": "Physics", "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fec2b295b085ab6eb91"], "topics": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "65c4c0c01d30997d3436baff", "title": "JEE Main 2024 (27 Jan Shift 2)", "isVisible": true}], "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "classes": [], "microConcepts": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616023caa70d3c7d1ad1a7cc", "616023cd679428937ef67e6c", "61964c7b4fcf164475aade2b", "61bb820d8bbe97a3447a9e67", "616023c9d383c4c41c614007", "616023c852e150b8704113a9", "61c08985a4ac848dc81e0d8f", "61964c7ab7812826e790a384", "61e7bd6fb80a936d82a83856", "616023cb9f0de15db281edb4", "629f3a923bbab6d5b2d9bb33", "629109f0e5beb8e92d681b24", "62962124c2093a5ec94418b0", "629f390ed92e81aeddcd3d6e", "64eb06be3118f713ecfef060", "66d58554a75f05ee8564f674", "67921d6b1d5b5072da5e9ae1", "67fdff64378e1624ea7b6af1", "680920293a10446a207fdece"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}